  </m:msub>
  <m:mo> ) </m:mo>
  <m:mi mathvariant="bold"> k </m:mi>



     </m:mtd>
   </m:mtr>

</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</equation></para>

<para id="element-79">Evidently, it is difficult to remember above expression. If we know to expand determinant, then we can write above expression in determinant form, which is easy to remember.
</para>
<para id="element-80"><equation id="equation-80">
